    "# Session 2 Further work\n",
    "These are example solutions of the further work given"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {},

   "source": [
    "# We always start with appropriate imports; note the use of the IPython magic\n",
    "# command to set up Matplotlib within the notebook\n",
    "%matplotlib inline\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Accuracy & Precision\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def approx_cos(x,dx):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Approximate cos(x) using approximate derivative of sine\"\"\"\n",
    "    return (np.sin(x+dx) - np.sin(x))/dx"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "With dx 1e-5, the error is  -4.207362275021609e-06\n",
      "With dx 1e-10, the error is  -5.848103645789138e-08\n",
      "With dx 1e-15, the error is  0.014809206444438505\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"With dx 1e-5, the error is \",approx_cos(1.0,1e-5) - np.cos(1.0))\n",
    "print(\"With dx 1e-10, the error is \",approx_cos(1.0,1e-10) - np.cos(1.0))\n",
    "print(\"With dx 1e-15, the error is \",approx_cos(1.0,1e-15) - np.cos(1.0))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "It is interesting that the error *increases* once we make `dx` too small.  This is related to rounding error and accumulation, and we will consider it more in Session 3."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Approximating reality\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1 (moon due to earth)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Set up time \n",
    "total_time = 2*365*24*60*60 # s\n",
    "days = 730 # Subdivision\n",
    "time = np.linspace(0,total_time,days)\n",
    "# Orbits\n",
    "period_ES = 365*24*60*60 # s\n",
    "period_ME = 28*24*60*60 # s\n",
    "\n",
    "# Physical constants, approximated\n",
    "radius_ES = 1.5e11 # m\n",
    "radius_ME = 3.8e8  # m\n",
    "mass_S = 2e30      # kg\n",
    "mass_E = 6e24      # kg\n",
    "mass_M = 7e22      # kg\n",
    "G = 6.7e-11        # m^3 /kg s^2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Position of Moon relative to Earth as a 2D array, starting on the x-axis\n",
    "pos_ME = radius_ME * np.array([np.cos(2 * np.pi * time / period_ME), np.sin(2 * np.pi * time / period_ME)])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5,1,'Acceleration of Moon considering Earth')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 6,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "a_ME = -G*mass_E*pos_ME/(radius_ME**3)\n",
    "plt.plot(time,a_ME[0])\n",
    "plt.plot(time,a_ME[1])\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Time/s\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Acceleration/ms^-2\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Acceleration of Moon considering Earth\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Question 2 (moon due to earth and sun)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5,1,'Moon-Sun distance')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "pos_ES = radius_ES * np.array([np.cos(2 * np.pi * time / period_ES), np.sin(2 * np.pi * time / period_ES)])\n",
    "pos_MS = pos_ME + pos_ES\n",
    "# Quick check\n",
    "plt.plot(time,pos_MS[0])\n",
    "plt.plot(time,pos_MS[1])\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Time/s\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Position in m\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Moon-Sun distance\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pos_MS_2 = pos_MS[0]*pos_MS[0] + pos_MS[1]*pos_MS[1]\n",
    "pos_MS_mag = np.sqrt(pos_MS_2)\n",
    "pos_MS_3 = pos_MS_2*pos_MS_mag\n",
    "a_MS = -G*mass_S*pos_MS/(pos_MS_3)\n",
    "a_M = a_MS + a_ME"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5,1,'Acceleration of Moon considering Earth and Sun')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 9,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.plot(time,a_M[0])\n",
    "plt.plot(time,a_M[1])\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Time/s\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Acceleration/ms^-2\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Acceleration of Moon considering Earth and Sun\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Note that this shows a significant effect from both Sun and Earth (though because we have assumed that the orbits are circular, these are a very crude approximation).  Look at the differences in mass and radius, and check that the influence is reasonable.\n",
    "\n",
    "## 5 Finding roots\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def newton_raphson(fun,dfun,x0,tol):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implementation of Newton-Raphson method for root finding.\n",
    "    Inputs: \n",
    "        fun is the function\n",
    "        dfun is the function's derivative\n",
    "        x0 is the starting guess\n",
    "        tol is the tolerance\n",
    "    Outputs: number of iterations and root\"\"\"\n",
    "    fx = fun(x0)\n",
    "    dfx = dfun(x0)\n",
    "    xcurr = x0\n",
    "    n = 0\n",
    "    while abs(fx) > tol: # We search for a root\n",
    "        n += 1\n",
    "        # Calculate next point\n",
    "        xcurr = xcurr - fx/dfx\n",
    "        fx = fun(xcurr)\n",
    "        dfx = dfun(xcurr)\n",
    "    return n,xcurr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Using NR, starting at -1.5 we find a root of  -1.0000000104979403  after  4  iterations\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def cubic_to_solve(x):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Calculate f(x) = x^3 - 2x^2 - x + 2\"\"\"\n",
    "    return x * x * x - 2 * x * x - x + 2\n",
    "def dcubic_to_solve(x):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Return df(x) = 3x^2 -4x -1\"\"\"\n",
    "    return 3 * x * x - 4 * x - 1\n",
    "\n",
    "nit, root = newton_raphson(cubic_to_solve,dcubic_to_solve,-1.5,1e-6)\n",
    "print(\"Using NR, starting at -1.5 we find a root of \",root,\" after \",nit,\" iterations\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def newton_raphson_check(fun,dfun,x0,tol):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implementation of Newton-Raphson method for root finding with checks.\n",
    "    Inputs: \n",
    "        fun is the function\n",
    "        dfun is the function's derivative\n",
    "        x0 is the starting guess\n",
    "        tol is the tolerance\n",
    "    Outputs: number of iterations and root\"\"\"\n",
    "    fx = fun(x0)\n",
    "    dfx = dfun(x0)\n",
    "    xcurr = x0\n",
    "    n = 0\n",
    "    while abs(fx) > tol: # We search for a root\n",
    "        n += 1\n",
    "        # Check for divergence\n",
    "        if abs(df/dfx) > 1e3:\n",
    "            print(\"Probable divergence found with df(x) \",dfx,\" after \",n,\" iterations.\")\n",
    "            return n, None # None signals a failure to find root\n",
    "        # Calculate next point\n",
    "        xcurr = xcurr - fx/dfx\n",
    "        fx = fun(xcurr)\n",
    "        dfx = dfun(xcurr)\n",
    "    return n,xcurr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def newton_raphson_bisection(fun,dfun,a,b,tol):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Implementation of Newton-Raphson method for root finding with initial bisection.\n",
    "    Inputs: \n",
    "        fun is the function\n",
    "        dfun is the function's derivative\n",
    "        a, b bracket the starting guess\n",
    "        tol is the tolerance\n",
    "    Outputs: number of iterations and root\"\"\"\n",
    "    # Start with bisection using tolerance of 1e3*tol (arbitrary!)\n",
    "    n = 0\n",
    "    fa = fun(a)\n",
    "    fb = fun(b)\n",
    "    while abs(b-a) > 1e3*tol:\n",
    "        n += 1\n",
    "        c = (a + b) / 2\n",
    "        fc = fun(c)\n",
    "        if fa*fc > 0:\n",
    "            a = c\n",
    "            fa = fc\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            b = c\n",
    "            fb = fc\n",
    "    # Now switch to NR\n",
    "    x0 = c\n",
    "    fx = fun(x0)\n",
    "    dfx = dfun(x0)\n",
    "    xcurr = x0\n",
    "    while abs(fx) > tol: # We search for a root\n",
    "        n += 1\n",
    "        # Calculate next point\n",
    "        xcurr = xcurr - fx/dfx\n",
    "        fx = fun(xcurr)\n",
    "        dfx = dfun(xcurr)\n",
    "    return n,xcurr"
   ]
  },

     ]

   "source": [
    "## 6. Optimising multi-dimensional functions\n",
    "\n",
    "### Question 1"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def function_2D(x,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Specified 2D function\"\"\"\n",
    "    return 1.5*x*x + 2*x*y + 3*y*y - x + 4*y\n",
    "\n",
    "def vector_dfunction_2D(x,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Vector differential of specified 2D function\"\"\"\n",
    "    df_dx = 3*x + 2*y - 1\n",
    "    df_dy = 2*x + 6*y + 4\n",
    "    return df_dx,df_dy"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def line_search(f,df,x,y):\n",
    "    \"\"\"Simple 2D line search\n",
    "    Inputs:\n",
    "    f, df  Function and vector derivative\n",
    "    x, y   Starting point\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Returns:\n",
    "    Value of lambda such that f((x,y) + lambda*df) is a minimum\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    lamb_curr = 0.0\n",
    "    lamb_new = 0.4\n",
    "    sd_x, sd_y = df(x,y)\n",
    "    # We need to search downhill, so change the sign!\n",
    "    sd_x = -sd_x\n",
    "    sd_y = -sd_y\n",
    "    print(\"Search direction: \",sd_x,sd_y)\n",
    "    fcurr = f(x,y)\n",
    "    fnew = f(x+lamb_new*sd_x,y+lamb_new*sd_y)\n",
    "    while fnew<fcurr:\n",
    "        print(\"l,ln,f,fn: \",lamb_curr,lamb_new,fcurr,fnew)\n",
    "        lamb_curr = lamb_new\n",
    "        fcurr = fnew\n",
    "        lamb_new = lamb_curr + 0.4 # Slow; we could multiply by a factor instead\n",
    "        fnew = f(x+lamb_new*sd_x,y+lamb_new*sd_y)\n",
    "    # Now we have two points bracketing the minimum\n",
    "    a = lamb_curr\n",
    "    fa = fcurr\n",
    "    b = lamb_new\n",
    "    fb = fnew\n",
    "    print(\"Brackets: \",a,b,fa,fb)\n",
    "    while abs(b-a)>1e-4: # This should be a user setting ideally\n",
    "        c = (a + b)/2\n",
    "        fc = f(x+c*sd_x,y+c*sd_y)\n",
    "        # Take an extra, small step to find which side of minimum c is on\n",
    "        fc_delta = f(x+(c+1e-3)*sd_x,y+(c+1e-3)*sd_y)\n",
    "        if fc_delta < fc: # We went downhill, so on the a side of minimum\n",
    "            a = c\n",
    "            fa = fc\n",
    "        else:\n",
    "            b = c\n",
    "            fb = fc\n",
    "        print(\"Brackets: \",a,b,fa,fb)\n",
    "    return c"
   ]
  },
